data.chText: 受到宠爱的；得到偏爱的；获得优惠的
data.enText: treated in a special way or receiving special help or advantages in a way that may seem unfair

data.chText: 总统宠爱的顾问班子中的一员
data.enText: a member of the President's favoured circle of advisers

data.chText: 他们的房子在公园附近一个很惬意的地段。
data.enText: Their house is in a very favoured position near the park.

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 favor

value.def: If you regard something or someone with favour, you like or support them.

example.ex: It remains to be seen if the show will still find favour with a 1990s audience...
example.tran: 这个节目是否能继续赢得 90 后观众的喜爱，还要拭目以待。

example.ex: No one would look with favour on the continuing military rule...
example.tran: 没有人会赞成继续军政府统治。

example.ex: He has won favour with a wide range of interest groups.
example.tran: 他已经获得众多利益集团的支持。

value.def: If you do someone a favour, you do something for them even though you do not have to.

example.ex: I've come to ask you to do me a favour...
example.tran: 我来这儿是想请你帮个忙。

example.ex: These are gestures of genuine friendship with no favours expected in return.
example.tran: 这是友谊的真正表现，不期待任何回报。

value.def: If you say that one person gives or sells their favours to another, you mean that they have sex.

example.ex: In her extreme youth, Maria had sold her sexual favours for money.
example.tran: 玛丽亚在非常年轻的时候，曾靠卖淫来赚钱。

value.def: If you favour something, you prefer it to the other choices available.

example.ex: The French say they favour a transition to democracy...
example.tran: 法国人说他们倾向于向民主过渡。

example.ex: He favours bringing the UN into touch with 'modern realities'.
example.tran: 他倾向于让联合国接触“当代现实”。

example.ex: The favoured candidate will probably emerge after private discussions.
example.tran: 中意的候选人很可能将在私下讨论后产生。

value.def: If you favour someone, you treat them better or in a kinder way than you treat other people.

example.ex: The Government came under fire yesterday for favouring elitist arts groups in the South-east...
example.tran: 昨天，政府因为偏袒东南部的一些精英艺术群体而遭到抨击。

example.ex: Another possibility is that parents favour chicks that are strong.
example.tran: 另一种可能性是亲鸟会偏爱强壮的雏鸟。

example.ex: Her younger brother was the favoured child, encouraged and admired by both parents.
example.tran: 她弟弟是个宠儿，受到父母双亲的支持和喜爱。

value.def: If you are in favour of something, you support it and think that it is a good thing.

example.ex: I wouldn't be in favour of income tax cuts...
example.tran: 我不会支持削减所得税。

example.ex: Yet this is a Government which proclaims that it is all in favour of openness...
example.tran: 但这却是个宣称全力支持开放的政府。

example.ex: The vote passed with 111 in favour and 25 against.
example.tran: 111 票赞成，25 票反对,表决通过。

value.def: If someone makes a judgment in your favour, they say that you are right about something.

example.ex: If the commission rules in Mr Welch's favour the case will go to the European Court of Human Rights.
example.tran: 如果委员会裁定韦尔奇有理，这个案件将送交欧洲人权法庭。

value.def: If something is in your favour, it helps you or gives you an advantage.

example.ex: The protection that farmers have enjoyed amounts to a bias in favour of the countryside...
example.tran: 农民所受的保护几乎变成了对乡村的偏袒。

example.ex: Firms are trying to shift the balance of power in the labour market back in their favour.
example.tran: 各公司正在试图让劳动力市场的均势向有利于自己的方向倾斜。

gramarinfo.label: n PHR, PHR after v, v-link PHR

value.def: If one thing is rejected in favour of another, the second thing is done or chosen instead of the first.

example.ex: The policy was rejected in favour of a more cautious approach.
example.tran: 这项政策未被采纳，取而代之的是一项较为谨慎的策略。

gramarinfo.label: PHR n, usu PHR after v

value.tran: (舍弃某物)宁愿选择;选…(而不选…)

value.def: If someone or something is in favour, people like or support them. If they are out of favour, people no longer like or support them.
